Package com.cafean.client.ui.beans

Interface PropertyController

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractIntegrationCase, AbstractReportData, Annotation, DataSource, EllipticalAnnotation, GeneralRange, ImageAnnotation, IntegrationCase, IntegrationDefinition, JobImporter, LineAnnotation, PolygonBean, QuickNote, RectangularAnnotation, SharedBoolean, SharedInteger, SharedIntegerWrapper, SharedReal, SharedRealWrapper, SharedString, SharedTable, SnapPreferences, TextAnnotation, UserDefinedConstant, UserDefinedVariable, ViewComponent
    public interface PropertyController
    An interface describing an object that has methods to determine if one of its properties is enabled or disabled, and optional or required at the current moment.

    This interface is used extensively in the Properties View to limit the properties displayed to those actually needed by the analyst.

      • isPropertyActive

        boolean isPropertyActive​(java.lang.String propertyName)
        Returns false if this object has a property with the given name that is considered inactive; otherwise true.

        The active active state of a property is separate from its enabled state to allow for optional properties that are actually a boolean paired with a property (i.e. value) of another type.

        Parameters:
        propertyName - a String containing the name of the property to check
        Returns:
        false if the property is inactive, true otherwise
        See Also:
        OptionalPropertyEditor
